\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fcolumns\u002Fbest-of-bbc-future\"\u003EDiscover more of our picks\u003C\u002Fa\u003E. &nbsp;\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWe all know that Brits speak differently depending on where they&rsquo;re from. But just how differently? And even if you&rsquo;re a non-British English speaker, might you share some vocabulary or pronunciations with people hailing from a UK region?\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFind out with our quiz. Inspired by academic research on accents and dialects, it tests which region of the UK has locals that speak the most like you &ndash; even if you&rsquo;re not British.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAre you a match for Hugh Grant, Cheryl or Ewan McGregor? Your geographic home may be far from the UK, but your linguistic home may be anywhere from Edinburgh to Belfast, London to the Lake District.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EYou might also like:\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003C\u002Fem\u003E\u003Cbr \u002F\u003E&bull; \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Fculture\u002Fstory\u002F20180207-how-americans-preserved-british-english\"\u003EHow Americans preserved British English\u003C\u002Fa\u003E \u003Cbr \u002F\u003E&bull; \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Fculture\u002Fstory\u002F20170619-why-british-english-is-full-of-silly-sounding-words\"\u003EWhy British English is full of silly-sounding words\u003C\u002Fa\u003E \u003Cbr \u002F\u003E&bull; \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Ffuture\u002Fstory\u002F20160202-has-the-queen-become-frightfully-common%20\"\u003EHow is the Queen&rsquo;s accent changing?\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003EQuiz developed by \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.vervesearch.com\u002F\"\u003EVerve Search\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E. Please note that Google Analytics is being used on this interactive; anonymised demographic result